The White House Office of the Press Secretary released a statement by NSC Spokesperson Ned Price on Japanese Prime Minister Abe's statement regarding the 70th anniversary of the end of World War II. The statement welcomes Prime Minister Abe's expression of remorse for the suffering caused by Japan during the war and his commitment to upholding past Japanese government statements on history. It also acknowledges Japan's commitment to peace, democracy, and the rule of law for the past 70 years and values Japan's intent to contribute to international peace and prosperity in the future.